abstract: The Nevada Democratic Party said on Tuesday it will not use the same app that led to delayed reporting of Iowa's Monday presidential caucus results for Nevada's caucuses on Feb. 22.
snippet: The Nevada Democratic Party said on Tuesday it will not use the same app that led to delayed reporting of Iowa's Monday presidential caucus results for Nevada's caucuses on Feb. 22.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Nevada Democratic Party said on Tuesday it will not use the same app that led to delayed reporting of Iowa's Monday presidential caucus results for Nevada's caucuses on Feb. 22.
headline_main: Nevada Democrats Will Not Use Reporting App That Led to Iowa's Delayed Caucus Results
headline_print_headline: Nevada Democrats Will Not Use Reporting App That Led to Iowa's Delayed Caucus Results

abstract: Alabama Sen. Doug Jones, widely considered the Senate's most endangered Democrat, voted Wednesday to convict President Donald Trump as the Senate impeachment trial concluded with Trump's acquittal — and Republicans will try to use Jones' vote against him as they seek to reclaim the once reliably red state.
snippet: Alabama Sen. Doug Jones, widely considered the Senate's most endangered Democrat, voted Wednesday to convict President Donald Trump as the Senate impeachment trial concluded with Trump's acquittal — and Republicans will try to use Jones' vote agai...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Alabama Sen. Doug Jones, widely considered the Senate's most endangered Democrat, voted Wednesday to convict President Donald Trump as the Senate impeachment trial concluded with Trump's acquittal — and Republicans will try to use Jones' vote against him as they seek to reclaim the once reliably red state.
headline_main: Vulnerable Democrat Doug Jones Votes to Convict Trump
headline_print_headline: Vulnerable Democrat Doug Jones Votes to Convict Trump

abstract: Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
headline_main: Partial Iowa Results Give Buttigieg Slight Edge Over Sanders
headline_print_headline: Partial Iowa Results Give Buttigieg Slight Edge Over Sanders

abstract: President Trump was cleared of both impeachment charges. Only Mitt Romney crossed party lines, the lone Republican who voted to convict and remove the president from office.
snippet: President Trump was cleared of both impeachment charges. Only Mitt Romney crossed party lines, the lone Republican who voted to convict and remove the president from office.
lead_paragraph: The Senate acquitted President Trump on Wednesday of charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress, as Republicans turned back an election-year attempt by House Democrats to remove him from office for pressuring a foreign power to incriminate his political rivals.

abstract: Global stocks rose Thursday after U.S. President Donald Trump was acquitted in an impeachment trial and China cut tariffs on U.S. imports and provided aid to businesses reeling from a virus outbreak.

headline_main: On Politics: Still Talking About Iowa

abstract: After almost 24 hours of delay, results from the Iowa caucuses have trickled in. Here’s what you need to know about the results and what they mean for New Hampshire.

abstract: There are many pitfalls on the road ahead.
snippet: There are many pitfalls on the road ahead.
lead_paragraph: On Monday night, the Iowa caucuses ended in chaos. More important, the partial results released on Tuesday suggest that the Democratic path to the White House remains rocky.
